text: Garðabær is a municipality in the Capital Region of Iceland. In 2019, 16,299 people lived there. The municipality of Álftanes was merged into the neighboring municipality of Garðabær in January 2013. == Twin towns == Garðabær is twinned with: * Asker, Norway * Eslöv, Sweden * Jakobstad, Finland * Rudersdal, Denmark == References == == Other websites == * Category:Cities in Iceland Category:Municipalities of Iceland Category:Capital Region (Iceland)
title: Garðabær
